Nevertheless, the predictive value of such a test can be questionned; the ranges of variation of the concentration of anti-asparaginase antibodies measured before the development of an allergic reaction overlap, they are respectively:
from 0.001 to 0.375 unit of OD for the patients who developed an allergic reaction subsequently;
from 0.004 to 0.064 unit of OD for the patients who did not develop a subsequent allergic reaction

According to an advantageous configuration, the method comprises the following stages:
(a) incubation of the sample with a known amount of asparaginase;
(b) incubation of the aforesaid mixture with a known amount of asparagine, preferably in an amount causing saturation relative to the amount of asparaginase;
(c) incubation of the aforesaid mixture with the reagent system that can provide assay of the residual enzymatic activity;
(d) qualitative or quantitative evaluation of the loss or retention of enzymatic activity, which correlates with the presence or the content in the sample, of factors that neutralize asparaginase activity.

Then the following procedure is followed:
(a0) optionally inactivation or removal of any asparaginase present in the serum sample, or measurement of the residual enzymatic activity
(a) incubation of the sample with 0.1 to 5 IU/ml of asparaginase for 1 to 60 min;
(a1) optionally removal of the immune complexes, preferably by centrifugation at 3000-25000g for 1 to 30 min at the specified speed;
(b) incubation of the mixture from (a) or of the supernatant from (a1) for 2 to 60 min with a saturating amount of asparagine, notably from 10 to 50 mg/ml;
(c) incubation, notably for 3 to 20 min, of the preceding mixture with the reagent system (α-ketoglutarate, NADPH, glutamate dehydrogenase) that is able to detect the residual enzymatic activity;
(d) qualitative or quantitative evaluation of the loss or retention of enzymatic activity, which correlates with the presence or the content of asparaginase neutralizing factors in the sample.

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren nach Anspruch 3, aufweisend die folgenden Stufen:
(a) Inkubation der Probe mit einer bekannten Menge der Asparaginase;
(b) Inkubation der vorgenannten Mischung mit einer bekannten Menge von Asparagin;
(c) Inkubation der vorgenannten Mischung mit dem Reagenssystem, das geeignet zur Prüfung der enzymatischen Restaktivität ist;
(d) qualitative oder quantitative Bewertung des Verlusts oder des Bewahrens von enzymatischer Aktivität, der/das mit der Anwesenheit oder mit dem Gehalt von neutralisierenden Faktoren der Asparaginase in der Probe korreliert ist.

The method according to Claim 3, comprising the following stages:
(a) incubation of the sample with a known amount of said asparaginase;
(b) incubation of the aforesaid mixture with a known amount of asparagine;
(c) incubation of the aforesaid mixture with the reagent system suitable for assaying the residual enzymatic activity;
(d) qualitative or quantitative evaluation of the loss or retention of enzymatic activity, which is correlated with the presence or with the content of neutralizing factors of said asparaginase in the sample.

Procédé selon la revendication 3, comprenant les étapes suivantes :
(a) incubation de l'échantillon avec une quantité connue d'asparaginase ;
(b) incubation du mélange précédent avec une quantité connue d'asparagine ;
(c) incubation du mélange précédent avec le système réactif apte à doser l'activité enzymatique résiduelle ;
(d) évaluation qualitative ou quantitative de la perte ou non de l'activité enzymatique, laquelle est corrélée à la présence ou à la teneur de l'échantillon en facteurs de neutralisation de cette asparaginase.
